  "text": "At least 2 experienced interventional cardiologists who were blinded to the patients' original status were required to make a consentaneous diagnosis. Coronary angiography was routinely performed using the Judkins technique in multiple projections without intravenous nitroglycerin. CAE was defined as an ectatic artery diameter !1.5 times that of adjacent normal segments. [CITATION_1] CAD was defined as !50% stenosis in one or more major coronary arteries. Subjects with 20% coronary artery stenosis were considered normal controls.",
